+{"id":"bd-1vr1","title":"Test coverage + e2e logging overhaul","description":"Goal: reach near-complete unit test coverage without mocks/fakes and add fully instrumented E2E integration suites with rich logging/diagnostics. This epic breaks down the work into baseline audits, harness/infra, mock-to-real conversions, and detailed E2E scenarios. Constraints: avoid mock.module()/mock data paths unless truly unavoidable; prefer real DBs, real services, and real CLI tooling. Success: unit tests exercise real code paths with integration-grade fixtures; E2E tests capture console/network/ws logs, traces, screenshots, and timing metadata for every scenario.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:25:28.297032911Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T05:21:43.570239810Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T05:21:43.570169909Z","close_reason":"All 13 children completed: baseline coverage, mock elimination, real DB harness, Playwright framework, gateway/web/package unit tests, E2E runner, agent lifecycle/DCG/reservations/beads/notifications E2E suites, and CI coverage gates with artifact retention.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-1vr1.1","title":"Baseline unit coverage + gap map (gateway/web/packages)","description":"Run bun test --coverage (and any package-level coverage tools) for apps/gateway, apps/web, and packages/* to establish current statement/branch/line/function coverage. Capture per-module gaps and hotspots (0% coverage files, critical services, WS hub, driver registry, etc.). Produce a concise baseline report (where results live, how to regenerate). Success: reproducible coverage commands + explicit list of uncovered modules.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:07.875242007Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T04:45:42.269604741Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T04:45:42.269537756Z","close_reason":"Baseline coverage report generated at docs/coverage-baseline.md. 207 files tracked, 25 with 0% fn coverage, 28 with <50% line coverage. Key blockers: test harness (bd-1vr1.3) needed for DB-dependent service tests.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"bd-1vr1.10","title":"E2E runner scripts: boot gateway+web with seeded DB","description":"Create a deterministic E2E runner that starts the gateway and web apps, seeds a fresh sqlite DB, exposes health checks, and tears down cleanly. Provide a single command for CI/local to run Playwright against a known-good environment. Success: E2E tests always run against a real backend with predictable data and no mock mode.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:28:03.478103732Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T04:35:53.962041097Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T04:35:53.961972188Z","close_reason":"Created e2e-server.ts script that boots gateway with temp seeded SQLite DB. Updated playwright.config.ts to auto-start servers via webServer config. Health endpoint verified working. Also fixed syntax error in ru-sweep.service.ts.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.10","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.10","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.10","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"bd-1vr1.11","title":"E2E: agent lifecycle + WS updates with rich logs","description":"Implement end-to-end Playwright coverage for agent lifecycle: spawn agent via API, observe state transitions, verify WS output/tool events, and UI updates across dashboard + agents pages. Use the logging framework to capture console/network/ws traces for each step. Success: deterministic E2E script validates lifecycle with full diagnostic artifacts.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:28:13.676702008Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T05:08:19.259459419Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T05:08:19.259386704Z","close_reason":"Created agent-lifecycle-e2e.spec.ts with 13 tests covering API spawn/terminate, WS connection, UI validation, error handling, and logging framework diagnostics.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.11","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.11","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.11","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"bd-1vr1.12","title":"E2E: DCG block/approve + audit trail","description":"Add E2E scenarios for DCG: simulate a blocked command, verify pending exception flow, approve via API/UI, and confirm audit logs + allow-once execution behavior. Capture all logs via the E2E logging framework. Success: DCG safety loop validated end-to-end with traceable artifacts.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:28:21.292960636Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T05:00:25.583767643Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T05:00:25.583691672Z","close_reason":"Created dcg-block-approve.spec.ts with 17 E2E tests covering full DCG lifecycle: block event ingestion, test/explain endpoints, pending exception approve/deny workflows, hash validation, audit trail stats/filtering, false positive marking, and UI workflow tests using the E2E logging framework (testLogger fixture).","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.12","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.12","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.12","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
-{"id":"bd-1vr1.13","title":"E2E: reservations + beads + notifications flow","description":"Create E2E coverage for reservation lifecycle, beads UI interactions, and notification delivery. Validate API + UI consistency and confirm real-time updates via WebSocket. Use structured logs from the logging framework to capture request/response and WS events. Success: end-to-end flow proves coordination features without mock data.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:28:33.265279513Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T18:31:47.897557277Z","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.13","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.13","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.13","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
