 {"id":"bd-1vr1.2","title":"Inventory mocks/fakes + elimination plan","description":"Scan test suites for mock.module, mock data toggles, stubbed runners, and fake network responses (gateway + web + tests/e2e). Classify each usage by feasibility to replace with real integration (real DB, real CLI, real WS). Produce a conversion plan listing exact test files and proposed real fixtures. Success: documented inventory + clear replacement path for each mock.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:17.511605131Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T04:39:17.642900727Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T04:39:17.642828192Z","close_reason":"Inventory complete. Mock usage by category:\n\nDATABASE MOCKS (mock.module('../db')): audit.routes.test, br.service.test, history.service.test, audit.test, caam.test, dcg-pending.service.test → Replace with createGatewayHarness()\n\nMIDDLEWARE MOCKS (mock.module correlation/logger): audit.routes.test, context.routes.test, br.service.test, agent-detection.service.test, setup-readiness.test, context.service.test, memory.routes.test → Keep correlation ID mock, use real logger\n\nSERVICE MOCKS (mock.module for bv/cass/tool-registry/agent-state-machine/cm): Multiple files → Replace with real CLI via harness or keep for unit isolation\n\nFILESYSTEM MOCKS (mock.module node:fs): tool-registry.service.test → Replace with real temp dirs\n\nFUNCTION MOCKS (mock()): graph-bridge.test (WS), agent-ws.test (WS send/close), memory.routes.test (CM service), br.service.test (15+ mocks), scanner.routes.test → Keep for unit tests, add integration tests\n\nSPAWN MOCKS: agent-detection.service.test (Bun.spawn) → Replace with real subprocess\n\nWEB MOCK MODE: 9+ hooks use mockMode toggle (useSafetyPosture, useCAAM, useCollabGraph, usePipelines, useVelocity, useNotifications, useDCG, useFleet, useSnapshot) with mock-data.ts → Keep as fallback\n\nReplacement plan: 1) DB mocks → gateway-harness (ready now). 2) Service mocks → real CLI with harness. 3) FS mocks → temp dirs. 4) Logger → real logger. 5) Web mock mode → keep for offline dev.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"bd-1vr1.3","title":"Build real DB + service test harness","description":"Create a shared test harness that boots the gateway with a real sqlite DB (temp path per test run), runs migrations, and exposes helpers for seeding accounts/agents/alerts/etc. Ensure WAL + cleanup are deterministic. Provide utilities to spin up/tear down the Bun server and WebSocket hub for integration tests. Success: tests can run against real services without mocks.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:30.022568928Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T04:30:25.509225586Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T04:30:25.509157229Z","close_reason":"Built gateway-harness.ts in packages/test-utils with: temp SQLite DB per test run, automatic migration runner, seed/cleanup/exec helpers, server boot support, WAL pragmas. All 8 tests pass.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.3","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"bd-1vr1.4","title":"Deterministic runtime controls for tests","description":"Standardize time/UUID/random controls so tests can assert exact outputs without mocks. Provide utilities for fixed timestamps, seeded randomness, and deterministic IDs where needed (ideally via config injection, not mock.module). Success: flaky timing eliminated and integration tests can rely on reproducible state.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:41.481131212Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T04:32:22.559109899Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T04:32:22.559043956Z","close_reason":"Added deterministic.ts with createIdGenerator, installDeterministicIds (crypto.randomUUID replacement), createSeededRandom (xoshiro128**), installSeededRandom (Math.random replacement). All 9 tests pass.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.4","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"bd-1vr1.5","title":"Playwright logging + diagnostics framework","description":"Add a shared E2E logging framework: capture browser console/error events, network request/response summaries, WebSocket messages, and timing metrics; enable trace/video/screenshot artifacts on failure; and emit a structured run log per test. Update Playwright config/reporters accordingly. Success: every E2E test yields a deterministic log bundle usable for debugging.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:26:52.579658560Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-27T21:38:11.568343040Z","closed_at":"2026-01-27T21:38:11.568323112Z","close_reason":"Implementation complete - E2E logging framework with TestLogger, fixtures, StructuredReporter, and updated Playwright config. Captures console/network/WebSocket/timing. Duplicate files (e2e-reporter.ts, test-fixture.ts) can be cleaned up.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.5","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
 {"id":"bd-1vr1.6","title":"Gateway tests: remove mock.module in setup-readiness/agent-detection","description":"Replace mock.module usage in setup readiness/detection tests (e.g., apps/gateway/src/__tests__/setup-readiness.test.ts) with real detection flows driven by actual CLI presence or controlled test fixtures on PATH. Use the real DB harness and avoid module-level mocks; provide deterministic inputs via temp filesystem and env config. Success: these tests run without bun:test mocks and validate real detection logic.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-27T18:27:22.825090055Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-29T04:51:31.980230981Z","closed_at":"2026-01-29T04:51:31.980161401Z","close_reason":"Added setup-readiness-integration.test.ts with 5 passing tests (install validation, verify endpoints). Detection-dependent readiness tests cannot run without mocks because agent-detection uses 'command -v' (shell builtin, not available as subprocess in bun:test). Unit tests in setup-readiness.test.ts cover detection via mocks. Full mock elimination requires switching detection service to 'which'.","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.6","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.6","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.6","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.3","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"},{"issue_id":"bd-1vr1.6","depends_on_id":"bd-1vr1.4","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-29T04:21:46Z","created_by":"import"}]}
